@startuml
' Author: Nicholas Irvine  GitHub https://github.com/SaladStik  LinkedIn https://www.linkedin.com/in/nicholas-irvine-303ab5284/
title Orbit GitOps with Argo CD

' Nobody runs `kubectl apply` by hand. Git holds the desired
' state. Argo CD keeps making the cluster match it.

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false

rectangle "Git repo (DESIRED state)" #e9f5ff {
  artifact "argocd/app-of-apps.yaml\n(orbit-root)" as root
  artifact "argocd/apps/*\n(child Applications)" as children
  artifact "k8s/** manifests\n(infra + services)" as manifests
}

rectangle "Argo CD (controller)" #fff5e9 {
  component "orbit-root\nApplication" as argoRoot
  component "child\nApplications" as argoChildren
}

rectangle "Kubernetes (LIVE state)" #e9ffe9 {
  node "namespace: orbit" as live
}

root --> argoRoot : watches
argoRoot --> argoChildren : app-of-apps\npulls in children
children --> argoChildren
argoChildren --> manifests : each child watches a path

argoChildren --> live : SYNC\n(reconcile to match git)
live --> argoChildren : reports drift

note bottom of argoChildren : selfHeal and prune push drift back. Change git to change the cluster.

@enduml
